1. *Pobegli* su od straha. (They ran away from fear.)
2. Oni su *pobegli* iz zatvora. (They escaped from prison.)
3. Kada smo stigli, gosti su već *pobegli*. (When we arrived, the guests had already fled.)
4. On je uspeo da *pobegne* od policije. (He managed to escape from the police.)
5. *Pobegao* je od kuće jer se svađao sa roditeljima. (He ran away from home because he was arguing with his parents.)
6. Bilo je mnogo ljudi koji su *pobegli* zbog ratnih sukoba. (There were many people who fled because of the war conflicts.)
7. Njihov pas je *pobegao* i još ga nisu našli. (Their dog ran away and they haven't found him yet.)
8. Kada je video zmiju, dečak je *pobegao* u strahu. (When he saw the snake, the boy ran away in fear.)
9. Rekli su mi da su svi *pobegli* iz grada pre nego što je počeo uragan. (They told me that everyone had fled the city before the hurricane started.)
10. Bilo je teško uhvatiti mačku koja je stalno *pobegavala*. (It was hard to catch the cat that was constantly running away.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "pobegli" is the past tense plural form of the verb "pobeći," which means "to run away" or "to escape." The word can also be used in other forms, such as "pobegao" (past tense singular masculine) and "pobegla" (past tense singular feminine).